# Source package constraints

This directory defines the Debian source-package metadata for
`fcitx5-grimodex`. It is deliberately **not offline-buildable** from a plain
GitHub source snapshot today.

The server uses SwiftPM dependencies pinned by `hazkey-server/Package.resolved`,
and the dictionaries, emoji data, and llama.cpp sources are pinned Git
submodules. Those sources are not vendored into this repository. `debian/rules`
does not download or initialize them; it fails early when the required
submodule content is missing. A build environment must provide Swift 6.1 or
newer and a pre-resolved SwiftPM cache, or a downstream source archive must
vendor all pinned SwiftPM sources and recursively include every submodule.

Consequently, this metadata is suitable for validating package identity and
for controlled downstream builds with prepared inputs. It must not be
submitted to an offline Debian archive builder until all build-time sources
and their license texts are included in the source archive (or represented by
Debian packages). Creating a `.dsc` proves the metadata is well-formed; it does
not prove an offline binary build.

The installed package retains the root `LICENSE` and `NOTICE.md` in
`/usr/share/licenses/fcitx5-grimodex`. A release builder is also responsible for
retaining every third-party license required by the recursively included
sources and statically linked Swift components.
